#### Simple reproducible example:

```php
<?php

class T {

    public function test(): string {
        return "test method";
    }

    public function test2($param): string {
        return $param . PHP_EOL;
    }
}

$t = new T();
echo <<< HTML
    <span>{$t->test()}</span>
    {$t->test2(<<< X
        something 
        something
    X)}
    HTML;
```

@tonihele that could very well be the case, in which case you might be able to fix this issue at your end in the short term.  Is the Linux one you said works also bundling a JDK?

I don't think we really have "some expert" to fix NBI.  At least, there has been minimal development on it since the donation to ASF, and a bunch of outstanding bugs.  We've already stopped releasing NetBeans using the Linux NBI support due to unresolved issues.  Personally, I think we'll switch the Windows installer one way or another too.  And even if we don't, the JDK bundling can't be used at ASF so it's possibly even less likely to get looked at.

If you want some help with NBPackage, let me know - happy to help and feedback would be a welcomed contribution to it right now!  You can also see how it's currently integrated into the main NetBeans release builds (for DEB and RPM so far) here - https://github.com/apache/netbeans-jenkins-lib/blob/master/vars/asfMainNetBeansBuild.groovy#L394
